status: MARC21-007: Specific material designation of tactile resource
Special class of tactile materialspecific material to which the item belongs.

definition (en): A system of writing for the blind in which letters, numerals, and punctuation are made of raised dots distinguishable by the fingers.
Combination of two or more types.
No text and only communicated as graphic, i.e. a raised line diagram or drawing.
Special material designation for the tactile material is not specified.
Specific material designation other than moon, braille, combination, tactile, with no writing system.
